# Alpha Bot Profitability Upgrade Walkthrough

I have analyzed the failure history and implemented several core improvements to transform the system into a "Good Program" that protects your capital and learns from its mistakes.

## 1. Analysis Result: "Conservative Mode" Activated
I ran the updated **Performance Monitor**, and it discovered that the recent prediction success rate was only **34%**. 
- **Action Taken**: The system has automatically updated its internal weights to **Conservative Mode** (Market 0.6 -> 0.5, News 0.3 -> 0.25). 
- **Result**: This will naturally lower the final scores, making the bot much more selective about which trades to enter during this low-accuracy period.

## 2. Key Improvements Applied

### 🛡️ Safety Fix: Fail-Safe Rejection
Previously, if the local AI server (Ollama) had an error or timed out, the bot would default to "APPROVE" and buy anyway.
- **Change**: I modified `llm_reasoning.py` so that any API error or exception now defaults to **REJECT**. No more blind buying during server glitches.

### 🧠 Self-Learning: Dynamic Weights
The "Left Brain" no longer uses fixed logic.
- **Change**: `brain_aggregator.py` now reads its weights from a file generated by `performance_monitor.py`.
- **Benefit**: As the market changes, the system will automatically favor the data sources that are currently working best.

### 📉 Risk Refinement
- **Trailing Stop**: Increased from 5% to **7%** to prevent being stopped out by normal market noise.
- **Kelly Fraction**: Lowered the minimum trade size from 5% to **2%**. This allows the bot to take smaller, safer positions when confidence is not at its peak.

## How to Verify
1. Open [brain_weights.json](file:///c:/Users/smile/%EC%95%8C%ED%8C%8C%EC%97%90%EC%9D%B4%EC%A0%84%ED%8A%B8/data/intelligence/brain_weights.json) to see the current self-calculated success rate and weights.
2. Restart your `alpha_master_launcher.py`. You will see "Conservative Mode" reflected in the Brain Aggregator logs.

We have now given the system a "conscience" and a "memory". It will now start to protect your principal much more aggressively.
